public_same_charge = []
private_same_charge = []
discount_schools = []

merged_df['discount_tuition'] = None

for index, row in merged_df.iterrows():
        
    # Get the name of the school out.
    name = row["name"]
    
    # Truth value.
    discount_tuition = True
    
    if (row["in_state_tuition"] >= row["out_of_state_tuition"]):    
        if (row["type"] == "Public"):
            public_same_charge.append(name)
        else:
            private_same_charge.append(name)
        
        discount_tuition = False
    else:
        discount_schools.append(name)
    
    # Set the truth value.
    merged_df.at[index, 'discount_tuition'] = discount_tuition    
    
print("The number of public schools that don't discount in-state tuition: " + str(len(public_same_charge)))
print("The number of private schools that don't discount in-state tuition: " + str(len(private_same_charge)))
print("The number of schools that discount in-state tuition: " + str(len(discount_schools)))

# Plot out-of-state tuition vs early and mid-career pay.

# Create a list of tuples for the variables that will be extracted out of the dataframe.
target_y = [("out_of_state_tuition", "Out Of State Tuition", "early_career_pay", "Average Early Career Pay", "mediumpurple"), 
            ("out_of_state_tuition", "Out Of State Tuition", "mid_career_pay", "Average Mid Career Pay", "mediumpurple"), 
            ("in_state_tuition", "In State Tuition", "early_career_pay", "Average Early Career Pay", "blue"),
            ("in_state_tuition", "In State Tuition", "mid_career_pay", "Average Mid Career Pay", "blue")]

# Create a dataframe of just the schools that discount in-state tuition.
discount_df = merged_df.loc[merged_df['discount_tuition'] == True]

for (var_x, title_x, var_y, title_y, color) in target_y:
    fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize = (9,6))
    
    df_to_use = merged_df
    
    if (var_x == "in_state_tuition"):
        df_to_use = discount_df
    
    ax.scatter(df_to_use[var_x], df_to_use[var_y], color = color)
    ax.set_xlabel("Tuition (Dollars)")
    ax.set_ylabel("Career Pay (Dollars)") 
    ax.set_title(title_y + " Vs. " + title_x)
    
    # Plot fit line.
    x_data = df_to_use[var_x]
    y_data = df_to_use[var_y]

    # Get polyfit p.
    p = np.polyfit(x_data, y_data, 1)

    # Get x_fit.
    x_fit = np.linspace(x_data.min(), x_data.max(), 1024)

    # Get y_fit.
    y_fit = np.polyval(p, x_fit)

    # Plot.
    ax.plot(x_fit,y_fit,'r-')
    
    # List out the slope equation for hte linear fit.
    (m, b) = p
    lin_fit_eq = "y = " + str(round(m, 2)) + " * x + " + str(int(b)) 
    ax.text(0.15, 0.90 ,lin_fit_eq, ha='center', va='center', transform=ax.transAxes)

# Violin Plots
bucket_groupby = merged_df.groupby('out_tuition_bucket')

# Violin plots
pay_groups = []
tuition_buckets = []

for bucket, bucket_df in bucket_groupby:
    pay_groups.append(bucket_df['early_career_pay'].tolist())
    tuition_buckets.append(bucket)

fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(12,6))
ax.violinplot(pay_groups, list(range(len(tuition_buckets))), showmeans=True)
ax.set_xticks(list(range(len(tuition_buckets))))
ax.set_xticklabels([int(x) for x in tuition_buckets])
ax.set_xlabel("Tuition Bucket Right Edge (Dollars)")
ax.set_ylabel("Early Career Pay (Dollars)")
ax.set_title("Violin Plot of Early Career Pay By Bucketed Out-Of-State Tuition")
fig.savefig("residual_violin.png", bbox_inches = "tight")

# Linfit time.

early_career_pay_lst = []
tuition_buckets = []
bucket_groups = []

for key, group_df in bucket_groupby:
    
    # Storing the life expectancies into the early_career_pay_lst.
    # Storing the year as well.
    early_career_pay_lst.extend(group_df["early_career_pay"].tolist())
    tuition_buckets.extend(group_df["out_tuition_bucket"].tolist())
    bucket_groups.append(key)
    
# Setting the array of arrays of life expectancy and the array of tuition_buckets as independent and dependent variables.
ind, dep = [ [elem] for elem in tuition_buckets], early_career_pay_lst

# Fitting the independent variables to the dependent set.
lm = linear_model.LinearRegression()
lm.fit(ind,dep)

# Exercise 3
residuals = [] 

# Iterating through the groupby object and getting the dataframe associated with each group.
# We'll use each group_df to extract a list of that year's life expectancies.
for key, group_df in bucket_groupby:
    
    # Calculate the predicted value.
    predicted_value = m * key + b
    
    # Calculate the residuals for the whole group_df and append it to the residuals list.
    residuals.append(list(map(lambda x: x - predicted_value, group_df["early_career_pay"].tolist())))

# Creating the violin plot using the example code.
figure(figsize=std_figsize)
rounded_bucket_groups = [int(x) for x in bucket_groups]
plt.violinplot(residuals, list(range(len(rounded_bucket_groups))), showmeans=True)
plt.xlabel("Tuition Buckets (Dollars, Rounded To Integer)")
plt.ylabel("Career Pay Residuals")
plt.title("Violin Plot Of Career Pay Residuals By Tuition Buckets")
plt.xticks(list(range(len(rounded_bucket_groups))), labels=rounded_bucket_groups)
plt.savefig("violin_residuals.png")
